        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 6:44PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 644 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Pope AFB, or 11 miles north of Fort Bragg, moving east
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lillington, Benson, Falcon, Erwin, Coats, Olivia, Dunn, Spring Lake,
Pineview, and Godwin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
